@startuml architecture
title Trilium ETAPI MCP — deployment

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor #F5F7FA
    BorderColor #8A94A6
    roundCorner 12
}
skinparam node {
    BackgroundColor #EEF2F7
    BorderColor #8A94A6
}
skinparam ArrowColor #4A5568

actor "MCP client\n(Claude Code, …)" as C1
actor "MCP client\n(other host / token)" as C2

node "Docker host / compose network" as Host {
    rectangle "reverse proxy\n(optional — TLS)" as Proxy #FFF6E5
    rectangle "mcp sidecar\n(this repo)\n:8081 /mcp" as MCP
    rectangle "trilium\n:8080 /etapi" as Trilium
    database "trilium-data\n(volume)" as Data
}

C1 --> Proxy : HTTPS /mcp\nAuthorization: <ETAPI token>
C2 --> MCP : HTTP /mcp (trusted LAN)\nAuthorization: <ETAPI token>
Proxy --> MCP : /mcp
MCP --> Trilium : ETAPI\n(token forwarded)
Trilium --> Data : reads / writes notes

note bottom of MCP
  Turns every ETAPI endpoint into an MCP tool
  (~40) at startup. Holds no secret — the client's
  token is the only credential.
end note

@enduml
